I. Import data 
  1. scan(file ='xxx') 
     rawdata = scan(file='stdin')
  2. readline(x)
     rawdata = file('stdin')
     open (rawdata)
     readlines(rawdata,n=1,warn=FALSE)
 
 II. Clean the data
  1. trimws() to remove white spaces
     trimws(x, which = c("both", "left", "right"), whitespace = "[ \t\r\n]")
     trimws(x) by default rm both sides' which spaces
  2. strsplit() to split character vecor x into substrings
     strsplit(x, split, fixed = FALSE, perl = FALSE, useBytes = FALSE)
     strsplit(x,' ')
  3. as.integer(x) to transfer sth into integers

III. Output a nice looking number
use cat(), cat is life-saving when a function returns horrible strings

